## SPM Parameter Tuning

### Key parameters to calibrate (in `configs/battery_params.yaml`)

| Parameter | Effect | How to calibrate |
|-----------|--------|-----------------|
| `Ds_pos`, `Ds_neg` | Diffusion speed → V dip during high C-rate | GITT pulse test |
| `cs_max_pos/neg` | Capacity | From full CC discharge |
| `stoich_0/100_soc` | SOC–OCV alignment | Slow OCV profile |
| `R_int` | IR drop | 10ms pulse test |
| `particle_radius` | Diffusion timescale | EIS or literature |

### Sanity checks after fitting

```matlab
% 1. Equilibrium voltage check (no current)
spm = buildSPM(battParams);
V_eq = spm.ocvPos(battParams.electrodes.positive.stoich_100_soc) - ...
       spm.ocvNeg(battParams.electrodes.negative.stoich_100_soc);
fprintf('Expected V at 100%% SOC: %.3f V (should be ~4.2 V)\n', V_eq);

% 2. Capacity check
Q_sim = simulatedCapacity(spm, battParams);
fprintf('Simulated capacity: %.3f Ah (expected: %.3f Ah)\n', Q_sim, battParams.cell.nominal_capacity_Ah);
```

